<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FCFFE4348A7515DFE2BFF5F" lastPageId="387" lastPageNumber="388" pageId="385" pageNumber="386" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FCFFE4248A7515DFAD7FF07" blockId="385.[151,1437,1649,2033]" lastBlockId="386.[151,1436,151,247]" lastPageId="386" lastPageNumber="387" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FCFFE4148A7515DFE14F979" bold="true" box="[151,433,1649,1674]" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FCFFE414AA9515DFC8CF979" box="[665,809,1649,1673]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="385" pageNumber="386" unit="mm" value="3.4" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="2.6">2.6–4.2 mm</quantity>
. Head brown, except anterior region of clypeus and mandible testaceous; antenna brown, except segments 1–2 and 8–10 whitish; mesosoma brown-testaceous; metasoma brown; forelegs brown, except chela testaceous, trochanter and part of coxa withish; mid- and hindlegs with tarsi and part of tibiae testaceous, part of coxae, trochanters and part of clubs of femora whitish. Antenna clavate; antennal segments of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCFFE4149C9502DFDFEF8E9" box="[505,603,1793,1817]" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">holotype</typeStatus>
in following proportions: 10:7:18.5:12:9.5:8:6:6:5:7.5. Head excavated, shiny, smooth, unsculptured in 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCFFE4149C45009FDFCF8CD" box="[500,601,1829,1853]" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">holotype</typeStatus>
. Head with frontal line complete, occipital carina absent; POL = 1.5; OL = 1.5; OOL = 11. Palpal formula 6/3. Pronotum shiny, smooth, unsculptured, crossed by strong transverse impression. Scutum dull, sculptured by longitudinal keels, without lateral pointes apophyses. Metanotum smooth, shiny, weakly hollow behind scutellum, with sides protruding; lateral protrusions rounded. Metathorax + propodeum of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCFFE41490F5099FE04F83D" box="[319,417,1973,1997]" pageId="385" pageNumber="386">holotype</typeStatus>
with anterior surface shiny, smooth, unsculptured; posterior surface strongly transversely striate. Mesopleuron and metapleuron almost completely smooth, unsculptured, partly transversely striate. Mesometapleural suture distinct and complete. Protarsal segments of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38FCCFE424B4357BBFC70FF5F" box="[883,981,151,175]" pageId="386" pageNumber="387">holotype</typeStatus>
in following proportions: 18:4:6:21:34. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FCCFE4249795790FE63FF24" box="[329,454,188,212]" captionStart="PLATE 120" captionStartId="386.[151,233,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[231,1376,286,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-149@386.[170,1414,259,1907]" captionTargetPageId="386" captionText="PLATE 120. A–C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, holotype. A. Gonatopus asiae (=Apterodryinus asiaticus) (from Olmi 1984). B. G. hagoromo. C. G. insulae (=Apterodryinus insularis) (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lini (courtesy of Michael Sharkey). Length 1.15 mm. E. G. lini (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.29 mm for A, 0.22 mm for B, 0.12 mm for C and 0.19 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278792/files/figure.png" pageId="386" pageNumber="387">Plate 120B</figureCitation>
) with one large subdistal tooth and one row of 8–11 lamellae + one hair. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FCCFE42493E57F3FE2FFF07" box="[270,394,223,247]" captionStart="PLATE 120" captionStartId="386.[151,233,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[231,1376,286,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-149@386.[170,1414,259,1907]" captionTargetPageId="386" captionText="PLATE 120. A–C, E. Chelae, holotypes. D. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, holotype. A. Gonatopus asiae (=Apterodryinus asiaticus) (from Olmi 1984). B. G. hagoromo. C. G. insulae (=Apterodryinus insularis) (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lini (courtesy of Michael Sharkey). Length 1.15 mm. E. G. lini (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.29 mm for A, 0.22 mm for B, 0.12 mm for C and 0.19 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278792/files/figure.png" pageId="386" pageNumber="387">Plate 120B</figureCitation>
) with two rows of 14–22 lamellae; distal apex with about 24 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<caption id="54B656C98FCCFE4248A7505DFE52F813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278792" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5278792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278792/files/figure.png" pageId="386" pageNumber="387" startId="386.[151,233,1905,1928]" targetBox="[231,1376,286,1897]" targetPageId="386">
